==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[mōros]]'' 'foolish'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/mɔrɒn/

===Noun===
'''moron''' (plural: [[morons]])

# A term for a mentally deficient person whose mental age is equivalent to that of someone between eight and 12 years of age.
# ''(Informal)'' A [[stupid]] person.
# George Kittner
:''Usage: Though a psychological, clinical, and medical term, it is often used as a pejorative term against someone of low intelligence, or even as just a general pejorative.''

